It seems like you're asking about the background picture or theme in your code. If you're referring to a background image in your project, it might be defined in your CSS, HTML, or JavaScript files. Look for something like this in your code:

### In CSS:
```css
body {
    background-image: url('path/to/your/image.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
}
```

### In HTML:
```html
<div style="background-image: url('path/to/your/image.jpg'); background-size: cover;"></div>
```

### In JavaScript:
```javascript
document.body.style.backgroundImage = "url('path/to/your/image.jpg')";
```

If you're asking about the theme or background in Visual Studio Code itself, you can change it by going to **File > Preferences > Color Theme** or by searching for "Color Theme" in the Command Palette (`Ctrl+Shift+P`).

Let me know if you need help finding or modifying the background in your project!

